{{Infobox scientist
|name        = Galina Kofman
|birth_place = {{flag|RUS|name=Russia}}
| nationality       = {{flag|USA|name=United States of America}}
| awards            = two IBM CEO Outstanding Technical Achievement Awards, 1990 and 1992
|known_for = IBM Kerberos, IBM FTP and NTP, [http://www.prweb.com/releases/2011/01/prweb4973354.htm Executive]
}}
'''Galina Kofman''' is a [[computer scientist]] and business executive. She was the author of [[Kerberos (protocol)]] for various [[IBM]] systems.<ref>[[Barry Appelman]]</ref> Kofman also authored [[FTP]] for IBM [[VM/CMS]] and [[OS/2]]. She received two IBM CEO Outstanding Technical Achievements awards and holds a patent on grid applications.<ref>[http://patent.ipexl.com/EP/EP1989622.html Method, system, and program product for deploying a platform dependent application in a grid - EPO Patent EP1989622]</ref> Kofman is an executive at [[Recyclebank]], a green company that rewards people for recycling.

== Career at IBM Research ==
While a researcher at [[IBM Thomas J. Watson Research Center|Thomas Watson Research Center]], Galina Kofman worked in the group of [[Barry Appelman]], a significant Internet notable and the inventor of instant messaging. Kofman was active in Internet protocols development and specifically in [[TCP/IP]] since 1983 with her first project of RLSS, a remote login system that was a predecessor of Telnet at IBM. Appelman's group as a whole proved critical in IBM's early embrace of the Internet despite having a competing family of protocols [[IBM Systems Network Architecture]]. Kofman authored Kerberos for [[OS/2]], [[VM/CMS]] and [[AIX]]. She also authored [[FTP]] client and server for VM/CMS and OS/2. Kofman also authored [[Network Time Protocol]] for various IBM operating systems.<ref>[https://groups.google.com/group/comp.protocols.time.ntp/tree/browse_frm/month/1992-05/168c4db40616a892?rnum=11&_done=/group/comp.protocols.time.ntp/browse_frm/month/1992-05?&hl=da&pli=1 Note on comp.protocols.time.ntp May, 1992]</ref><ref>[http://diswww.mit.edu/menelaus.mit.edu/kerberos/1235 MIT Kerberos discussion, Feb 7 91]</ref> Kofman also was active in algorithms related to processing unstructured text.<ref>[http://domino.watson.ibm.com/library/cyberdig.nsf/papers/1898F3F640FEF47E8525723C00551250/$File/rc24122.pdf IBM Research Report, "Towards An Interoperability Standard", 2006]</ref> Kofman was the program manager and the main developer of IBM Magic system in 2006<ref>[http://domino.research.ibm.com/library/cyberdig.nsf/papers/CD71D3BB49C6454F852571B0005622E1/$File/rc24002.pdf IBM Research report, "MAGIC",2006]</ref> According to Recyclebank press release, Galina Kofman received 2 IBM CEO Outstanding achievement awards, one in 1990 and another in 1992.

== Career after IBM ==
Galina Kofman is currently an executive at [[Recyclebank]], a green company.<ref>[http://www.prweb.com/releases/2011/01/prweb4973354.htm Recyclebank press release]</ref>

