{{Eastern Slavic name|Magomedovich|Murtazaliev}}
'''Sagid Magomedovich Murtazaliev''' ({{lang-ru|Сагид Магомедович Муртазалиев}}; {{lang-av|СагIид МагIамедович МуртазгIалиев}}; born 11 March 1974) is a Russian [[freestyle wrestling|freestyle wrestler]]. Born in [[Makhachkala]], [[Dagestan]] and of [[Avar people (Caucasus)|Avar]] descent, Murtazaliev has won gold medals in heavyweight divisions at the [[1999 FILA Wrestling World Championships|1999 FILA World Championships]] and the [[2000 Summer Olympics]].

==Olympics==
Murtazaliev represented Ukraine at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in Atlanta, and represented Russia at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], where he won gold in the [[Wrestling at the 2000 Summer Olympics – Men's freestyle 97 kg|men's freestyle 97 kg]] competition.<ref name=db-ol-WRE2000>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=WRE "2000 Summer Olympics &ndash; Sydney, Australia &ndash; Wrestling"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080907043524/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=WRE |date=2008-09-07 }} ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on September 9, 2008)</ref><ref name=sref>{{cite web|title= Sagid Murtazaliyev |url= https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mu/sagid-murtazaliyev-1.html |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref>

In 2013, he returned his medal to the IOC in protest of its vote to briefly drop wrestling from the Summer Olympic programme.<ref>[https://archive.is/20130412043402/http://www1.whdh.com/news/articles/sports/olympics/10009966025023/russian-wrestler-to-return-his-olympic-gold/ Russian wrestler to return his Olympic gold]</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/wrestling/21654061|title=Bulgaria wrestling coach Armen Nazaryan on hunger strike|date=2013-03-04|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-05-26|language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Politics==
In 2001, a bomb was found near Murtazaliev's home in [[Kizlyar]].<ref>{{cite web | title =Nail Bomb Discovered | work =Archives | publisher =The Russia Journal | date =February 10, 2001 | url =http://russiajournal.com/archive/The_Russia_Journal/2001/February/10.02.2001/Analysis/Feb.10-03.pdf | format =pdf | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref> A charitable foundation is named after Sagid Murtazaliev.<ref>{{cite web | title =A charitable foundation of the Olympic champion from Dagestan Sagid Murtazaliev plans to develop sports in Kizlyarski district of Dagestan | work =Sports | publisher =Ria Dagestan | date =July 24, 2007 | url =http://www.riadagestan.com/news/2007/07/24/2394/ | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref> On April 12, 2010, Murtazaliev, who had been the head of [[Kizlyarsky District]], became the head of the Dagestan branch of the Russian pension fund.<ref>{{cite web | last =Troshina | first =Albina | title =Sagid Murtazaliev is the new head of Branch of the Pension fund of Russia in Dagestan | work =Politics | publisher =Ria Dagestan | date =April 13, 2010 | url =http://www.riadagestan.com/news/2010/4/13/5007/ | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =Scandalous replacement of head of Pension Fund in Dagestan | work =Week in the Caucasus: review of main events of April 19–25 | publisher =Caucasian Knot | date =April 26, 2010 | url =http://abhazia.eng.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/13197/ | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref> Murtazaliev was a [[United Russia]] party deputy to the Legislative Assembly of the Republic of Dagestan.<ref>{{cite web | title =Speaker of the Dagestan Parliament hands in cards to deputies | work =Politics | publisher =Ria Dagestan | date =April 18, 2011 | url =http://www.riadagestan.com/news/2011/4/18/6301/ | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =Сагид Муртазалиев: "Нужно вникать в проблемы людей…" | work =Новости | publisher =Moi Dagestan | date =March 4, 2011 | url =http://moidagestan.ru/news/society/5051 | accessdate =September 10, 2012 }}</ref> In 2015, the prosecution office opened a criminal case against Murtazaliev on financing terrorism as well as suspected him in relation to a number of murders. Murtazaliev left Russia and is currently wanted by the prosecution.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dp.ru/a/2017/07/07/Test_beglogo_glavi_dages|title=Тесть экс-главы дагестанского ПФР Муртазалиева, обвиняемого в убийствах, свел счеты с жизнью|last1=Горошков|first1=Павел|last2=Васильева|first2=Марина|date=7 July 2017|publisher=dp.ru|language=Russian|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref>

