{{Buddhism}}

'''Supushpachandra''' ([[Sanskrit]]: ''Supuṣpacandra'') is the name of a [[bodhisattva]] mentioned by [[Shantideva]] in the ''[[Bodhisattvacaryāvatāra]]''.{{sfn|kun bzang dpal ldan|2007|p=169}} He was ordered by royal law to abstain from teaching [[Buddhism]], but ignored the statute and was executed by King Shuradatta. An account of his tale can be found in the ''[[Samadhiraja Sutra]]''.{{sfn|kun bzang dpal ldan|2007|p=169}}

